SEC. 3. The Commission shall have the following powers and duties.

To investigate and conduct studies of all active Philippine volcanoes;

To establish necessary facilities in order to predict their eruption in advance, if possible;

To formulate in advance and in detail specific plans of action and of relief in the event of the eruption of any volcano;

To recommend to the President of the Philippines such measures as may be necessary to protect life and property in areas which may be affected by volcanic eruptions, including the declaration of certain areas as closed to human habitation or subject to regulation, as provided in section four hereof; and

To perform such other duties as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this Act.
